@node Why "Call 1.11"

     Why amigaguide?
     ===============

     Because hypertext is a great, and because owners of no amigaguide reader
     can read the doc anyway.

     And YES, this might seem to be an overworked manual to a small an pretty
     lousy coded and not usuable program.
     I just wanted to say that I found it sort of funny to release a doc-file 
     that was bigger than the program itself.

@endnode
@node Tips "Call 1.11"

     Loudspeakproblems.
     ==================

     This progam demands a loudspeaker to work and not i.e. the built in one
     in A4000T.
     The 1084 monitor has a very bad loudspeaker and to make it work with those you'll
     have to choose the volume close to were the distortion begins. Otherwise
     many telephones wount be able to recive the tones.

     Telephoneproblems.
     ==================

     Some telephones have a very bad microphone and therefor they can't
     recive the tones... This should only be a problem with very old or
     very cheap telephones.

     AXE services.
     =============

     As you might already know, AXE-phones has three more buttons than a "normal"
     telephone. They are #, * and R. This program can't simulate the R button
     simply because the R button have no tone. It's rather like closing the line
     for a short while. Therefor you can do this yourself, without R button!
     Just close the line for a tenth of a second and VOILA you have just simulated
     the R button...
@endnode
